Steps to Reproduce:

1. Create a button widget and add an TouchEventListener to it, call replaceScene, crashes on 
```c++
CCASSERT(!_running, "Node still marked as running on node destruction! Was base class onExit() called in derived class onExit() implementations?");
```

Sample code tested:
```c++
    auto backBtn = Button::create("btn.png", "btn.png", "btn.png")
    backBtn->addTouchEventListener([&](Ref *sender, Widget::TouchEventType type) {
    		if (type == ui::Widget::TouchEventType::ENDED)
    		{
    			auto loginScene = LoginScene::createScene();
    			loginScene->autorelease();
    			Director::getInstance()->replaceScene(loginScene);
    		}
    	});
    ;
```

I have never overrided onExit() of any of my classes.
The current Scene which is being replaced by new scene, is similar to this [tutorial](http://cocos.sonarlearning.co.uk/docs/scenes)

Possible duplicates: 
Issue #12483
Issue #10834

