I have the following code to create a multipart POST request with the HttpRequest class. In my App I send a JPG image to my server. This code works fine under Android / iOS / Mac / Win32. However, under WinUWP this code corrupts my image. The image is somehow splitted and the bottom part is cut away. My server appears to receive multiple corrupted/splitted files instead of one.

The WinUWP Network class uses a different code path than the other OS right? Maybe something is wrong there? So far I didn't manage to narrow down the problem cause any further.

Remark: I tried to transfer the image as base64 encoded string. Same problem. It doesn't seem to be related to the payload. But I discovered that the request length on the server is always around 130KB. It seems to be truncated at this length. On Win32 for example the length is correct (same length as on the client).

```
HttpRequest* createMultipartRequest(const std::string& requestUrl, const Json::Value& jsonPart, const std::string& binaryPath)
{
        HttpRequest* request = new (std::nothrow) HttpRequest();
        request->setUrl(requestUrl.c_str());
        request->setRequestType(HttpRequest::Type::POST);
        
        std::string boundary = "---------------------------14737809831466499882746641449";
        
        std::vector<std::string> headers;
        headers.push_back("Accept: application/json");
        headers.push_back("Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=" + boundary);
        request->setHeaders(headers);
        
        std::stringstream ss;
        ss << "--" << boundary << "\r\n";
        ss << "Content-Disposition: form-data; name=\"json_data\"\r\n";
        ss << "Content-Type: text/plain; charset=utf-8\r\n";
        ss << "Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit\r\n\r\n";
        ss << JsonUtils::writeToString(jsonPart);
        
        Data data = FileUtils::getInstance()->getDataFromFile(binaryPath);
        std::string binaryName = binaryPath.substr(binaryPath.find_last_of('/') + 1);
        
        ss << "\r\n--" << boundary << "\r\n";
        ss << "Content-Disposition: attachment; name=\"" << binaryName << "\"; filename=\"" << binaryName << "\"\r\n";
        ss << "Content-Type: application/octet-stream\r\n";
        ss << "Content-Transfer-Encoding: binary\r\n\r\n";
        ss << std::string((char*)data.getBytes(), data.getSize());
        ss << "\r\n--" << boundary << "--\r\n";
        
        std::string multipartStr = ss.str();
        request->setRequestData(multipartStr.data(), multipartStr.size());
        return request;
}
```
